	},
	"next_comment_id": 7,
	"comment": {
		"1_1HUrhTUZFB2KKsXLUv1vugPH358iB6zsiY": [
			{
				"comment_id": 1,
				"body": "> [kaffie](#comment_160_1NWh3WAty57FH8at1WtrZigMrdhrDkuPzh): Yup. As long as you give people the URL and they start seeding it, they can interact with and join the hub. The only thing is that it won't appear in the defaults, so if people aren't seeding it, they won't see the option to join it.\n\nBut I tested it with another PC and I saw it in the defaults.",
				"added": 1471481607
			},
			{
				"comment_id": 2,
				"body": "And the address is\n##18FheQ1v3bz4iv5yx8hr9hg5W5BJ8WNJ8d##",
				"added": 1471481663
			},
			{
				"comment_id": 3,
				"body": "> [kaffie](#comment_162_1NWh3WAty57FH8at1WtrZigMrdhrDkuPzh): See ZeroMe's content.json:\n> \"default_hubs\": {\n>    \"1BLueGvui1GdbtsjcKqCf4F67uKfritG49\": {\n>     \"description\": \"Hub for ZeroMe users. Runner: Nofish\",\n>     \"title\": \"Blue hub\"\n>    },\n>    \"1GrEenUGRWnzaNZjR3XsQa6dQgdPDTyt7i\": {\n>     \"description\": \"Hub for ZeroMe users. Runner: Nofish\",\n>     \"title\": \"Green hub\"\n>    }\n>   }\n> Only green and blue are defaults. So if you don't have any hubs downloaded, only those two will appear. This has been thoroughly tested. There's several hubs that have been created and don't show up at all unless you're already seeding them (at which point they show up under 'seeded hubs').\n> Could you provide a screenshot of a non-default hub showing up under the default hubs with the 'download' button? I've yet to see this happen.\n\nGreen?!\nI saw a red hub!(And the blue hub)",
				"added": 1471481848
			},
			{
				"comment_id": 4,
				"body": "http://127.0.0.1:43110/0chan.bit/?/b/thread/726f14851ba9230341f4c506ed433586\nScreenshot, and the red hub did disappear.",
				"added": 1471485139
			},
			{
				"comment_id": 5,
				"body": "> [kaffie](#comment_165_1NWh3WAty57FH8at1WtrZigMrdhrDkuPzh): Those are seeded hubs. Any hub you're seeding will appear there. Other people cannot see the things you do under 'seeded hubs' (they see their seeded hubs instead). The ones everyone see are listed under 'available hubs' and only contain green/blue as of now. They have a 'download' button next to them, and when downloaded, move over to the 'seeded hubs' section.\nYou are right. Once I stopped seeding on the test machine, I can't see yellow hub.",
				"added": 1471501690
			},
			{
				"comment_id": 6,
				"body": "And thank you all for help seeding it.",
				"added": 1471501944
			}
		]
	},
	"comment_vote": {
